{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/checkout-git-pull-request-locally-like-pro/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"itsopensource"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"34ab9a17-d370-56de-9b02-9624388b7282","excerpt":"If you work with the repositories hosted on Github , you have to deal with lot of Pull requests daily generally, and the process to checkout the PR’s locally in…","html":"<p>If you work with the repositories hosted on Github , you have to deal with lot of Pull requests daily generally, and the process to checkout the PR’s locally in your machine is quite not easy, you have to see the PR’s id and also the branch name.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> fetch origin pull/ID/head:BRANCHNAME</code></pre></div>\n<p>And if the PR is in upstream repository, first you need to add that particular user as remote in your local copy of the project and then pull the particular branch of the contributor. For example</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> remote <span class=\"token function\">add</span> fayem git@github.com:fayepal/itsopensource.git\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout -b fayem fayepal/blog-docker-vm</code></pre></div>\n<p>As we see its quite long process and you will have lot of remote added in your repository as well.</p>\n<p>To solve this there is a awesome <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/gnarf/5406589\">git alias</a> by gnarf:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>alias<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">pr</span>  <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"!f() { git fetch -fu <span class=\"token variable\">${2<span class=\"token operator\">:-</span>$(git remote |grep <span class=\"token operator\">^</span>upstream || echo origin)}</span> refs/pull/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>/head:pr/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> &amp;&amp; git checkout pr/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>; }; f\"</span>\n  pr-clean <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"!git for-each-ref refs/heads/pr/* --format='%(refname)' | while read ref ; do branch=<span class=\"token variable\">${ref<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>refs<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>heads<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>}</span> ; git branch -D <span class=\"token variable\">$branch</span> ; done\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Either you can add them directly in your <code class=\"language-text\">.gitconfig</code> file or by doing so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> config --global alias.pr <span class=\"token string\">'!f() { git fetch -fu <span class=\"token variable\">${2<span class=\"token operator\">:-</span>$(git remote |grep <span class=\"token operator\">^</span>upstream || echo origin)}</span> refs/pull/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>/head:pr/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> &amp;&amp; git checkout pr/<span class=\"token variable\">$1</span>; }; f'</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> config --global alias.pr-clean <span class=\"token string\">'!git for-each-ref refs/heads/pr/* --format=\"%(refname)\" | while read ref ; do branch=<span class=\"token variable\">${ref<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>refs<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>heads<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>}</span> ; git branch -D <span class=\"token variable\">$branch</span> ; done'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now you simply do <code class=\"language-text\">git pr x</code> and it will do the magic for you:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/5c1ad/1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 41.21621621621622%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"1\"\n        src=\"/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/1c72d/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/a80bd/1.jpg 148w,\n/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/1c91a/1.jpg 295w,\n/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/1c72d/1.jpg 590w,\n/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/a8a14/1.jpg 885w,\n/static/0adebf903922390684a72e24aacf84ea/5c1ad/1.jpg 1172w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Cheers</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to checkout github pull requests locally like Pro","tags":["git","github","howto"],"date":"September 27, 2020","description":null,"author":"shivam","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5037593984962405,"src":"/static/304ca8ee14d138750c6b49094a6f0bcf/14b42/git.jpg","srcSet":"/static/304ca8ee14d138750c6b49094a6f0bcf/f836f/git.jpg 200w,\n/static/304ca8ee14d138750c6b49094a6f0bcf/2244e/git.jpg 400w,\n/static/304ca8ee14d138750c6b49094a6f0bcf/14b42/git.jpg 800w,\n/static/304ca8ee14d138750c6b49094a6f0bcf/47498/git.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/checkout-git-pull-request-locally-like-pro/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/what-is-the-difference-between-docker-and-a-virtual-machine/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"faye","tags":["docker"],"title":"What is the difference between Docker and a Virtual Machine"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/content-security-policy/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"trishul","tags":["privacy","javascript"],"title":"Content Security Policy - protect your website from XSS attacks"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4268877247","764694655"]}